![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

The `playedPar` function includes the par of the current active hole as soon as the user records a single throw on it. This causes the scorecard's total score vs par to calculate incorrectly during an active round (e.g., showing `-3` when the user has only thrown 1 stroke on a Par 4 hole). Replace `playedPar` with helpers that only sum completed holes (where `index < currentHoleIndex`) during an active round.

```typescript
export function completedStrokes(session: GameSession): number {
	const limit = session.completedAt !== null ? session.course.holes.length : session.currentHoleIndex;
	return session.strokes.slice(0, limit).reduce((sum, s) => sum + s, 0);
}

export function completedPar(session: GameSession): number {
	const limit = session.completedAt !== null ? session.course.holes.length : session.currentHoleIndex;
	return session.course.holes.slice(0, limit).reduce((sum, hole) => sum + hole.par, 0);
}
```

![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

Update the scorecard to use the new `completedStrokes` and `completedPar` helpers. This ensures that the scorecard footer totals only reflect completed holes during an active round, preventing misleading relative scores (like showing `-3` on a Par 4 hole after 1 throw).

```
import {
	formatScoreVsPar,
	completedPar,
	completedStrokes,
} from "./gameState.ts";
import { distanceMeters, formatDistance } from "./geo.ts";
import type { GameSession } from "./types.ts";

const { session }: { session: GameSession } = $props();

const strokesTotal = $derived(completedStrokes(session));
const parTotal = $derived(completedPar(session));
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

In `placePoint`, calling `invalidateShareCode()` will set `statusMessage` to `'Course changed...'` if a share code exists. However, this message is immediately overwritten by the placement mode status messages (e.g., `'Tee ... set...'` or `'Hole ... added.'`), making it invisible to the user. Add an optional parameter to `invalidateShareCode` to control whether it updates the status message.

```
const invalidateShareCode = (showStatus = true) => {
	if (shareCode && showStatus) {
		statusMessage = "Course changed. Save again to refresh the share code.";
	}
	shareCode = null;
};
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

Pass `false` to `invalidateShareCode` here to prevent it from setting a status message that will be immediately overwritten by the placement instructions.

```
const placePoint = (point: LatLng) => {
	invalidateShareCode(false);
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

Overwriting `statusMessage` with a geolocation error during active tracking can be highly disruptive to the user (e.g., clearing active placement instructions like `'Tee 1 set — now place its basket'`), especially since the user can still place points manually by tapping the map. Consider logging the error to the console instead of showing it in the status bar, similar to how it is handled in `MapGame.svelte`.

```
		(error) => {
			console.warn("Position watch error:", error);
		},
```

